title: Vida Sobre Rodas
description:
Life On Wheels
"The documentary tells the history of Brazilian skate even be considered by many surveys as the second most practiced sport in Brazil today. That is since the 70s when the state of the sport in Brazil was bleak with almost no clue and no support for practitioners. Names such as Bob Burnquist, Sandro Dias, Lincoln Ueda and Cristiano Mateus represent a generation that reached the top of the skating world. True national heroes through resilience and persistence became life examples to be followed by all generations in Brazil."
